How to use the lads_downloader.py
- create and environment (pyVPRM) following: 
	conda config --add channels conda-forge
	conda config --set channel_priority strict
	conda install -c conda-forge dask netCDF4
	conda install esmf
	conda install esmpy
- modify the config.yaml:
	- set the start and end dates for the period of interest
	- add the list of tiles you want to download
- create a token.txt with the token you will get from: https://urs.earthdata.nasa.gov copy the string without the word "bearer" in the first line of the txt
- run the gen_tasks.py
	- beware of modifying the sys.path.append("/work/mj0143/b301034/Scrapbook_Analysis/Projects/pyVPRM/pyVPRM")
	- execute: export N=$(python gen_tasks.py) 
- go to: download_modis_new_parallel.py and modify also the sys.path.append("/work/mj0143/b301034/Scrapbook_Analysis/Projects/pyVPRM/pyVPRM")
- the previous two steps are not needed if you have pyVPRM installed in your environment
- mkdir logs
- modify the download_modis_new_submit.sh
	- create the OUTPUT_DIR 
	- change the OUTPUT_DIR path
- submit the job like:
sbatch --array=1-${N}%20 download_modis_new_submit.sh
- The script downloads all doy in a year for the tiles given. The start and end on the config file are just to provide the years. 
 
 
